# Eco Group: .eco&nbsp;champion

## {{{excerpt}}}

![{{header-img-alt}}]({{header-img}})

_We spoke with Aaron Barber, Managing Director at Eco Group, about how they are supplying more sustainable packaging to eco-conscious UK businesses._

### What is EcoGroup and what kinds of products do you make?

Eco Group is a UK-based sustainable manufacturer that brings together **labels**, **packaging**, **signage** and **print consumables** under one roof. Through our core divisions including Eco Labels, Eco Pouches, Eco Signs and Eco Toners, we help organisations simplify procurement while reducing the environmental impact of everyday products.

We specialise in bespoke label solutions for sectors such as food, logistics, healthcare and retail, alongside sustainable packaging formats, eco-conscious signage and environmentally responsible print consumables. All products are designed to meet real-world performance requirements while offering more responsible material choices, including recycled, recyclable and FSC-certified options.

Our approach is built around giving customers a single, reliable supply partner that can deliver consistent quality, strong service levels and measurable sustainability improvements. By combining multiple product categories into one group, we help businesses reduce supplier fragmentation, improve efficiency and make more sustainable decisions across their entire supply chain.

### What is the environmental impact of product packaging? How do you work to minimize it?

Packaging has a significant environmental impact across its full lifecycle, from raw material extraction and manufacturing through to transport, usage and disposal. Poor material choices and inefficient logistics can increase carbon emissions, generate unnecessary waste and contribute to landfill or pollution challenges.

At Eco Group, we focus on reducing this impact at every stage. We prioritise responsibly-sourced materials such as recycled content, FSC-certified papers and recyclable or compostable options wherever possible. We also work closely with customers to optimise specifications, ensuring they are fit for purpose without over engineering or excess material use.

Our production processes are designed to minimise waste and improve efficiency, while our logistics are structured to reduce emissions through smarter packing and carbon-conscious delivery methods. Any unavoidable emissions are measured and offset as part of our carbon neutral certification.

