Ultimately, our role is to help customers make better informed decisions, balancing cost, performance and environmental responsibility without compromise.

### What types of customers do you serve? Why do they choose your company?

We work with a broad range of organisations, from SMEs and fast-growing consumer brands through to large multi-site businesses and public sector organisations. Our customers operate across industries including food and drink, manufacturing, logistics, healthcare and facilities management.

Customers typically come to us for two key reasons. First, they want to reduce costs without sacrificing quality. Second, they are under increasing pressure to improve their environmental impact and need a partner who can deliver both.

We differentiate by combining commercial and environmental value. This includes offering a full audit of existing products, identifying opportunities to reduce costs, improve performance or switch to more sustainable materials. We also provide fast turnaround times, stock holding options and a reliable UK-based supply chain.

Importantly, we focus on transparency. Customers trust us because we provide clear, practical recommendations rather than generic sustainability claims. That balance of cost saving, service and credible environmental improvement is why many customers choose to work with us long term.

### What has becoming carbon neutral certified meant for your business?

Becoming carbon neutral certified has been a significant milestone for our business, both operationally and commercially. It has formalised our commitment to measuring, reducing and offsetting emissions across our entire operation, rather than treating sustainability as a marketing exercise.

